p Bipolar disorder occurs when you lose sight of undeniable fact that <em>this too shall pass</em> or <em>the only constant in life is change</em>.
p Introverts believe that things will become more and more and more stressful, until the stress overwhelms and kills them. So they hold back; they try to stay where it’s safe and avoid the danger; they want to go back into the known past. Even after the cycle has already passed the peak and is on its way down again.
p Extroverts believe that things will become more and more and more boring, until the boredom overwhelms and kills them. So they rush forth; they try to move on to where it’s interesting and embrace the danger; they want to jump forward into the unknown future. Even after the cycle has already passed the trough and is on its way up again.
p You cannot change where you are in the cycle. You can change the clock so it is pointing to a later hour; you cannot change yourself so that you are an hour in the future. You can change the clock so it is pointing to an earlier hour; you cannot change yourself so that you are an hour in the past.
